kpi_info.title: period_duration
kpi_info.use: Duration of the measurement period in minutes.

kpi_info.title: MAX_AVAIL_R99_CE
kpi_info.use: The maximum number of available R99 Channel Elements. In Ultrasite EUBB WCDMA BTS, the counter is the maximum amount of working baseband resources (HW capacity). In Flexi Rel2 & Flexi Rel3 WCDMA BTS when baseband pooling is not used, the counter is the maximum amount of R99 CE licensed capacity + R99 CE capacity of hybrid CFs. In Flexi Rel2 & Flexi Rel3 WCDMA BTS when baseband pooling is in use, the counter is the maximum amount of Local Cell Group dedicated baseband pool R99 CE licensed capacity + R99 CE capacity of hybrid CFs + total amount of licensed R99 CEs in the common baseband pool - licensed R99 CEs used by other Local Cell groups from the common baseband pool at the counter sampling moment. Note: If HW capacity available for LCG is less than licensed capacity then HW capacity is indicated in the counter. UPDATED: When the HW or the licensed capacity changes in the BTS.

kpi_info.title: AVG_AVAIL_R99_CE
kpi_info.use: The average number of available R99 Channel Elements. In Ultrasite EUBB WCDMA BTS, the counter is the average amount of working baseband resources (HW capacity). In Flexi Rel2 & Flexi Rel3 WCDMA BTS when baseband pooling is not used, the counter is the average amount of R99 CE licensed capacity + R99 CE capacity of hybrid CFs. In Flexi Rel2 & Flexi Rel3 WCDMA BTS when baseband pooling is in use, the counter is the average amount of Local Cell Group dedicated baseband pool R99 CE licensed capacity + R99 CE capacity of hybrid CFs + total amount of licensed R99 CEs in the common baseband pool - licensed R99 CEs used by other Local Cell groups from the common baseband pool at the counter sampling moment. Note: If HW capacity available for LCG is less than licensed capacity then HW capacity is indicated in the counter. UPDATED: The counter is updated over the measurement period. The value of the counter is the average value from all the samples during the measurement period.

In Flexi Rel2 & Flexi Rel3 WCDMA BTS when baseband pooling is not used, the counter is the minimum amount of R99 CE licensed capacity + R99 CE capacity of hybrid CFs. In Flexi Rel2 & Flexi Rel3 WCDMA BTS when baseband pooling is in use, the counter is the minimum amount of Local Cell Group dedicated baseband pool R99 CE licensed capacity + R99 CE capacity of hybrid CFs + total amount of licensed R99 CEs in the common baseband pool - licensed R99CEs used by other Local Cell groups from the common baseband pool at the counter sampling moment. Note: If HW capacity available for LCG is less than licensed capacity then HW capacity is indicated in the counter. UPDATED: The counter is updated when the HW or the licensed capacity changes in the BTS.

kpi_info.title: MAX_USED_R99_CE_DL
kpi_info.use: "The maximum number of used R99 Channel Elements in Downlink direction. The counter includes R99 CEs and hybrid CFs used by R99 users + CSoHSPA users that are allocated to R99 CE licensed area + R99 CEs consumed for CCHs. Note: CCHs consume R99 CEs only in case of Rel. 2 HW. In Rel. 3 and mixed Flexi BTSs (Rel. 3 + Rel. 2) CCCH processing sets are consumed instead. Only additional CCHs are calculated; that is, CCH capacity included in HW price is not visible in counters. Note: In Flexi Rel2 and Flexi Rel3 BTS, the number of used R99 CEs can temporarily exceed the licensed capacity when PS radio bearer bit rate is upgraded. Updated: The counter is updated over the measurement period. The value of the counter is calculated every 5 seconds. Samples are based on the maximum used R99 channel elements in the DL direction."

kpi_info.title: BTS_R99_CE_UTIL_UL_CLASS_1
kpi_info.use: The counter shows how many utilization rate samples have been detected within the (0 - <50)% class per uplink direction. Each utilization rate sample calculates the total number of R99 Channel Elements in use divided by the number of all available (licensed) R99 CEs. UPDATED: The counter is incremented when the sample of the utilization rate is within (0 - 50)% class.
